A kangaroo fetus develops in its mother's womb for 1 week then goes dormant until it's older sibling leaves mom's pouch. It then takes a little over 30 days for it to be born, and another week or two for mom to get pregnant again.
Female kangaroos lick a trail from their birth canal to their pouch. The tiny joey follows this saliva trail, crawling by grabbing the momma kangaroo's fur with it's forepaws. It then latches on to a nipple in the pouch and the nipple swells so the baby can't fall off.
A baby kangaroo can fit in a teaspoon.
A group of kangaroos is called a mob, troop, or court.

You Are 35 Years Old
35
Under 12: You are a kid at heart. You still have an optimistic life view - and you look at the world with awe. 13-19: You are a teenager at heart. You question authority and are still trying to find your place in this world. 20-29: You are a twentysomething at heart. You feel excited about what's to come... love, work, and new experiences. 30-39: You are a thirtysomething at heart. You've had a taste of success and true love, but you want more! 40+: You are a mature adult. You've been through most of the ups and downs of life already. Now you get to sit back and relax.
What Age Do You Act?

Yea, you know who you are. I haven't spoken to you in ages, but your presence left a lasting impression, for lack of better wording. It is 2:20 am, and I'm tired.

But its not just for one person. It applies to alot of the people in my life, including (most likely) the person reading this right now (thats you).

Also, sort of for a good friend of mine I've seen more of recently, and also, someone who probably will never read this. Oh well. I still wish them happiness.

Two months. That's 1/6 of a year. That's how long I've been with my baby.

Yea, I know you all think I'm crazy and I should dump him.

But I love him. And things aren't how they used to be.

I'm different with him. And my grades are improving. That's good, right?

We have things we have to work out. But so does everyone.


Oh well. See ya guys later.

--Christie

I want everyone who reads this to ask me three questions, no more [and] no less. Ask me anything you want. Then I want you to go to your journal, copy and paste this, allowing your friends (including myself) to ask you anything.

 

ok people, shoot.

Yesterday was my baby's birthday. We went to FIU for the MTV Campus Invasion thing. That was his best friend's gift. I got him a book he wanted, and this really cute bookmark. He was dying to get his hands on it, but he wasn't going to buy it till it came out in paperback. I just cut his waiting time to none. OH! I saw Sammy yesterday!! :) Haven't seen her in AGES!! AND I have a new sidekick!! She's so cute :P She's like a foot shorter than me. I saw soooo many people at the concert. Between people I was introduced to, and people I already knew, I said hi to roughly fifty people.
Yea, I know I told Emilio about 40, but I forgot to count some people I saw upstairs, and I saw another 8 or 9 people after he left.



It was my baby's birthday, and he had fun, so that's all that matters. (How many of you are getting sick yet?)

I got home exhausted, and I had class this morning. Guess what we did in class. What? I think I heard it coming from the gentleman in the back. Can you repeat that? You are correct! Aerobic Dance. Johnny, tell him what he's won! So, after coming home exhausted, fighting with my mom, waking up still exhausted, and fighting with my mom again, I had to go through an a little more than half an hour of aerobic dance. I'm so glad I'm finally on "spring break". I enjoy my one day. :P

blah.. this ghost i saw on sunday.. my mom saw him a few days b4 also. gunna go eat now, but ill be back. ill write about my april fools day, n sum weird ass dream i had a few days ago. shoulda known this was gunna happen.

stay tuned!

I scared someone last night, or rather, a group of someones- or were they noones? I couldn't tell. Either way, I went to McDonald's and there were these kids- 2 girls sitting in a shopping cart, and three guys, I think, pushing or pulling the cart- in front of us in the drive thru. I thought it was hilarious, so I took a picture (or three). I guess they got in trouble for going through the drive thru in a cart ("We want to be treated like a car, damn it!") and on foot rather than a car so they just left really quickly. I wanted to ask them if they wanted copies of the pictures, so I followed them, but they freaked out, so they started running away. I figured they would get a little scared, but aparently I underestimated my abilities. ;)


I thought that was funny.
